metadata.name: Dans le Noir #63
metadata.description:
Flos in the dark space,
Scarlet and blue in her own pearl,
Vexed with its own delights,
She put her face towards the quiet transparent,
Cold was the dream of the night,
Colours like new minted fruit,
Swift blown through the melodious air,
Keep the light evening with a transient dream,
Split a some white sheet of lightning.
_

Generative visual composition, hybrid techniques, animation, textures source created with GAN, assist by AI, layers transform in autonomous system, eclectic, colors, additional algorithm, modular patch, and combine with other elements that made with code.

metadata.name: System α #227
metadata.description:
"To capture the fleeting time in the generating process."

In this work,I d'like focus on the generating of generative art system itself rather than imitate some scene or style.
And with the flow of time, try to figure out where it can take me toward.

This work would be a series of my alternative view on generative art.
"α" means the first step of this series.

Press [s] in live view to save file as PNG.
Press [p] to stop.

------
Happy first birthday fx(hash) !!

20% of primary revenues go to Savepakistan Flood Relief Fundraiser.
20% of primary revenues go to the Processing foundation.

metadata.name: Ode to Random #66
metadata.description:
This simple minimalist generative token is a tribute to randomness. The underlying grid, the start and end of the colored shapes, the color styles, the transitioning point from order to chaos, are randomized. The names behind the Styles of this token are derived from artists who have greatly inspired me, all or most of whom have incorporated randomness or chaos in their art in one way or another.

The price and number of editions were also chosen using a pseudorandom number generator.

Embrace the random!

Made in p5js
Created December 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Careful with That Axe, Eugene #17
metadata.description:
This artwork imagines Eugene cutting through the canvas with an axe. It's coded entirely in p5.js and draws lines mimicking strokes of an ink pen on a paper canvas-like texture.

Best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called ‘Careful with That Axe, Eugene' by Pink Floyd: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V-HYayT1vwg

Artwork loads at 1000px by 1000px resolution by default. Press ‘2’,’4’ or ‘8’ to load as 2000px by 2000px, 4000px by 4000px or 8000px by 8000px respectively.
Press 's' at any time to download the rendered resolution.

metadata.name: Joy Spaces #115
metadata.description:
Sharing a space that fills us with happiness
    Exploring what is deeply inside 
    Thinking as one and thinking as hive
    We play
    A doing so we transcend

    I know you as you know me
    You explore as I explore
    Mirrors of fears to grow
    Mirrors of love to embrace
    Let's keep on as we can
    Discovering the unknown
    That explodes inside each of us
    And is asking to be felt



Controls: 's' - canvas save

Crafted to be seen in Google Chrome 107.0.5304.107

Released on fx(hash) to celebrate the first birthday of this platform that has transformed our lives and our culture. Thank you mates, developers, artist and collectors. It has been a great year and I hope is the first of many to came.

metadata.name: Improvisation I #166
metadata.description:
“Improvisation I“ was born after my experiments with Fractal Brownian Motion. 

During random tweaks of colours, parameters and sizes I got something that really clicked with me — a picture I wanted to get out of the code some time ago. 

Painterly looking curves and blots with subtle colours transitions create a calming picture, sometimes resembling outlines of a landscape.

——————

To change the size of an image, open it in live view and add ‘&size=[size (6800 max.)]’ to the end of the URL. 
Press [C] to load a clean version without grain.
Press [S] to save the image.

Created using p5.js and GLSL.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Oct. 2022.

metadata.name: Притяжение #141
metadata.description:
Inspired by Kazimir Malevich works, “Притяжение” features the connection between shapes, their positions and colours.
Although, as the work tries to develop further into a non-objective world, some real sceneries can still be associated with it.

Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

metadata.name: Sunset in Paradise #16
metadata.description:
Hundreds of Walkers descend the screen drawing a sky, sea and the sun reflection; creating a twilight scene of a sunset or possibly a sunrise depending on which coast your paradise can be found. 
Features - 32 Palettes 
5 Possible background colors per palette
3 different complexities of sky:
	-Refined - 3 colors (25% chance)
	-Complex - 5 colors (25% chance)
	-Normal - 4 colors (50% chance)
2 possible border colors: 
	Matching the sun color (40% chance) 
	Matching the sea color (60% chance)
2 different stroke thickness: 
	Fine (25% chance) 
	Medium-point (75% chance) 
Different amounts of Walkers for Sky, Sea and reflection.

Made by @p1x3lboy in p5.js
June 2022
